STMicroelectronics N.V. is a global semiconductor firm that designs, develops, makes and markets a range of products, including discrete and standard commodity components, and application-specific integrated circuits for analog, digital and mixed-signal applications. The company has market cap of $15.51 billion. The Company’s divisions include Automotive and Discrete Group (ADG), Analog and MEMS Group (AMG), Microcontrollers and Digital ICs Group (MDG), and Others. It has a 48.47 P/E ratio. ADG comprises all dedicated automotive Integrated Circuits (ICs), and discrete and power transistor products.
